The paper discusses zero-shot learning (ZSL) which is a subfield of computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). The paper also mentions the use of visual attributes and semantic word vectors which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) fields, indicating a possible connection to these subfields as well. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. cs.CL and cs.MM are less likely but still possible due to the mention of semantic relatedness and the use of visual features, respectively.
